<br>
I think it would have been cool for the designers to put level barriers in place on the road to 60 (50 pre-Kunark). The way it is now, people can just grind their way merrily along to whatever level they feel is good without taking the time to actually interact with the game world.<br>
<br>
I think it would have been fun to have planned it so that when you reach level 10, you gain no more experience until you fufill a certain quest. For low levels this could be pretty easy like killing your first Leatherfoot and turning in his cap for DEF's or killing your first Sarnak for Iksars etc. Fufilling this quest would get you a low level item plus allow you to gain experience to 20 or some other higher level. They could put these quests every 10 levels or something and make them progressively harder but upon completing, you would get better, class specific items and be allowed to progress into the next level bracket.<br>
<br>
I think a lot could have been done with this idea. VI has been looking at ways to slow XP gain and &quot;grinding&quot; and this would be a good way to do it (EQ2) plus would require that people interact more with the world and do more questing. There would be problems of course - making the quest items so that everyone could find them and no bottlenecks like Ragefire, making it so that you wouldn't require an uberguild to get your high levels (maybe a group encounter would be required, but nothing on the scale of needing 50 60+ people to get items) etc. I know this is just daydreaming and hindsight is alwys 20/20 but I think it is a cool idea that I haven't heard proposed before.<br>
Vulrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uderganpuppyeater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dergan Puppyeater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/10/02 12:24:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2882.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> In reply</span><hr size=1> I would assume an idea like this was not implemented due to how unpopular it would be. Everquest is just fine how it is (er, take that with a grain of salt)...<br>
<br>
Er, what I mean is, I like how EQ allows you the choice of playing however you want. Wanna get 60? Then grind your way up. Wanna just use it as a big interactive chatroom? Then don't fight monsters. Wanna concentrate on trade skills? Knock yourself out. (And get a sponsor...)<br>
<br>
If they put a limit on leveling like that, it would just take away from the sense of being able to do anything and go anywhere in the world. Besides, what RP sense does that make? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umylodifv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MylodiFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/10/02 12:42:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2882.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In reply</span><hr size=1> Having to complete a quest in order to gain the next level would be really cool. <br>
<br>
Imagine having to go all the way back to your newbie location and talk to so and so, who gives you an item to take to so and so halfway across the world. When you talk to him, he summons a dragon which you and your group have to kill. Get the dragonscale off the dragon and give it to your guild leader and *poof* Level 61 is yours. <br>
<br>
Would be really cool.  <p>Mylodi ScarlettFyre, Bard of 44 cycles<br>
